trans-unit.source: Contains a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
<xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> objects are used to map specific security levels to named policy files.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> class.
Adds a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> to add to the collection.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> objects from the collection.
If <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection> entries exist in the local node collection, all entries are deleted.
Gets the type of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> object.
A value from the <xref href="System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollectionType"></xref> enumeration representing the type of the collection.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object at the specified index.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> at the specified index.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> item at the specified index within the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> object.
If a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> object exists at the specified index, the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> object is removed and a new one is added.
If no <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> object exists at the index, a new one is added.
The numeric index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref>.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> at the specified index.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object at the specified index.
A <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> object must exist at the specified index within the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection> object.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref>.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> that exists at the specified index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
Removes a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> object.
If the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel> object does not exist in the local node collection, no error is raised.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
Removes a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object at the specified index location from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> object.
The index location of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> to remove from the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> object to the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref> object at the specified index.
The index location of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> to be set within the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevel"></xref> to be set within the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TrustLevelCollection"></xref>.
